name: yan jiang
headline: Looking for challenging job
creator: False
current_company: 乐普(北京)医疗器械股份有限公司
bio:
Yan Jiang has both Bachelor and Master of Biomedical Engineering with focus on  medical image processing, biomechanics, medical device design and finite element modeling (FEM). She has three years experiences on FEM, especially for irregular and inhomogeneous objects (human bone) with isotropic material properties (bone material properties were assigned by bone mineral density system). Her major work is to design and execute the whole modeling, simulation and validation process, investigate the sensitiveness of FE model, and establish the protocol and workflow of the model generation procedure. She also has extensive experiences working with different CAD tools and Matlab-Simulink. 

research interests: 
Biomechanics, Finite element modeling; Model simulation and validation; Clinical rehabilitation, Medical imaging processing; Gait Analysis, and so on.

name: Sabine Beuk
headline: I train and support good business to build their commercial foundation and scale their societal impact - Generous Minds
creator: True
bio:
So, you know that scaling a business is great but also a struggle? Ambitious impact and growth targets but little time and resources to get you there. This is where I can support you. I help good business optimize their commercial foundation to achieve more impact and growth. 

I simultaneously educate people to work and live from their authentic self, because I strongly believe if more people do this our world is a better place. 

My focus is on companies contributing to a better and more fair world for all 🌍

I support companies to: 
✅ enable growth and impact
✅ create go to market strategies 
✅ integrate a data-driven way of optimizing conversions, growth hacking
✅ enable companies to run a successful crowd- sharefunding campaign
✅ start optimizing conversions with Selling- & Negotiating from Authenticity
✅ create deeper connection in teams to unlock untapped energy and reach business goals faster
✅ create more headspace for Founders/MT

I do this in the following ways: 
1️⃣  Training - I train commercial teams in amongst others data driven experimentation, Selling from Authenticity, Negotiating from Authenticity, Account Management. I train management- and project teams in Authenticity at Work
2️⃣  Commercial Booster Program - I work with start-up/scale-up Founders and their team during 3-5 months to optimize their commercial foundation and increase conversions
3️⃣  Interim - I support Founders/MT as an interim Commercial Manager or as a Campaign Manager
4️⃣  1:1 Coaching - I train and coach individual entrepreneurs that are excellent in their expertise, but do not like to sell their own service/product

In general I'm also always keen to meet new people with new perspectives, so don't hesitate to send me a message 🙌

Marktlink is the leading independent M&A-specialist for small and medium sized enterprises (SMEs) in the Netherlands.

Marktlink assists entrepreneurs with:
Mergers | Acquisitions | Financial Due Diligence | Valuations | Financing | Management Buy-Outs (MBO) and Buy-Ins (MBI) | Pre-exit.

We at Marktlink Transaction Services assist you during your financial due diligence, in both acquisition as vendor processes. Due diligence ensures an overview of financial risks and opportunities, and provides you with strong input for negotiations.

On a yearly basis over 100 M&A transactions are completed successfully with a team of approximately 175 professionals in five Dutch offices; Amsterdam, Deventer, Drachten, Gouda and ‘s-Hertogenbosch. Internationally, Marktlink has offices in Antwerp, Hamburg, Copenhagen, Manchester and Düsseldorf.

Do you have a company you want to sell? Do you want to buy a company? For more information about the due diligence possibilities contact Marktlink Transaction Services via +31 (0) 6 45 78 60 70 or via e-mail s.hoolwerf@marktlink.com.

name: Mathijs Matser
headline: Solution Architect at Salesforce Marketing Cloud
creator: False
bio:
From a young age, my interests extended to economics and numbers in particular. This passion led me to pursue education in the field and delve into various work experiences and extracurricular activities to deepen my understanding.

As a professional, I have had the privilege of working for leading companies across diverse industries, including FMCG, sports, advertising, and ad tech. Throughout my career, I have developed a strong affinity for data and marketing, leveraging this expertise to deliver impactful solutions for both B2B and B2C clients. In my current role at Salesforce, I specialize in consulting clients on how to maximize their martech capabilities, empowering them to achieve their business objectives.

Outside of my day-to-day job, I like to expand my horizons, which ultimately led me to continue my career journey in Australia. There, I learned to work with different cultures, challenge my status quo, and think outside the box. More recently, back in the Netherlands, I have embarked on a journey to become a certified breathwork coach as I found out that I was struggling with breathing, which affected my performance at work. I now try to help others with my findings and facilitate positive change in the lives of those around me.

Let's connect if my profile sounds of any interest to you and explore opportunities to collaborate.

bio:
My talent is leading a project team in grasping complex challenges and shaping result driven actions for the team and myself while practicing a beginners mind. I communicate in a confident manner at various levels within an organization to set priorities and goals, and to inspire the team to deliver creative solutions to our customers. I enjoy bringing engineering and science to society and I am very conscious of the qualities of my team members. 

That’s why I enjoy working as an innovative project manager of a multidisciplinary team in which I can bring out the best in people. I hold a PhD in experimental physics and have 26 years of professional experience in R&D, prototyping and production. I am an enthusiastic professional combining a proven substantive background with a business entrepreneurial drive.

name: Robin Dekker
headline: Financial Controller en Business Controller bij Batenburg Digit/Batenburg Bellt/Batenburg Industriële Automatisering
creator: False
school_2: HBO A&A Hogeschool voor de Accountancy
bio:
Ervaren financial en business controller met een brede verantwoordelijkheid binnen vier werkmaatschappijen van de Batenburg Industriële Automatisering divisie. Met een scherp oog voor cijfers én buitengewone affiniteit met processen draag ik bij aan het optimaliseren van financiële sturing, resultaatverbetering en strategische besluitvorming. 

Mijn professioneel kritische instelling als gevolg van jarenlange ervaring in de accountancy combineer ik met mijn kracht in het combineren van analytisch inzicht met een pragmatische aanpak. Optimaliseren van processen? Liever vandaag dan morgen! Of het nu gaat om budgettering, analyseren van resultaten en het ondersteunen van directies met heldere managementinformatie – ik zorg voor financiële grip én overzicht.
